---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Eyebrow from "../components/Eyebrow.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main class="intro">
    <section class="intro-card">
      <Eyebrow text="about">
        <h1>Welcome</h1>
      </Eyebrow>

      <div class="content">
        <p>I started on Neopets.</p>
        <p>
          Now I untangle enterprise systems for the automotive industry. My title says
          Leading Technical Consultant, but my days look like hands-on engineering
          with a backend bias. I can step up as a tech lead, but I'd rather be in the
          code. Brownfield or greenfield, legacy or launch-day — I work across the
          stack to make complex things simple and tangled code clear. I'm also the
          person who sits with the customer, asks the annoying questions, and finds
          the requirements they forgot to mention. That usually means code, sometimes
          means CI/CD or infrastructure, and lately it means figuring out what to ask
          an LLM to get useful answers back.
        </p>
        <p>
          That Neopets part matters. I learned this because I wanted to, not
          because I had to.
        </p>
      </div>

      <a class="cta" href="/skills">Checkout my toolbox</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .intro-card {
    width: min(100%, 44rem);
    border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: clamp(var(--space-6), 4vw, var(--space-8));
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
  }

  .content {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .intro-card p {
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .intro-card .cta {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
